Hilal Browser: enable native blurred macOS chrome surfaces

Makes Hilal top-level macOS windows non-opaque, installs a real
macOS vibrancy surface behind the browser chrome, and removes the CSS-only
backdrop-filter fallback that left the desktop wallpaper directly readable.
The Hilal background element mirrors Zen Browser: the element itself is
native-themed with -moz-sidebar so Gecko can emit sidebar theme geometry, while
the tint is painted on pseudo-elements so native theming is not suppressed by
author-specified backgrounds.

Hilal also forces a full-window Sidebar vibrancy region from Cocoa for top-level
windows, so toolbar and sidebar blur do not depend on the browser-box layout or
on whether a CSS frame happened to register theme geometry. This is the actual
NSVisualEffectView path that obscures wallpaper details.

Also ports Zen Browser's WebRender opaque-backdrop fallback so CSS
backdrop-filter surfaces remain well-defined inside transparent windows. The
desktop/wallpaper blur itself is provided by NSVisualEffectView vibrancy, not
by CSS opacity.

